- 2.0.2 | Feb 20 2026:

[Change] ipset batch loading via ipset restore; replaces per-entry $IPSET add
      loop (31K+ fork+exec calls) with single awk pre-filter piped to
      ipset restore -exist, reducing load time from minutes to seconds
      (functions.apf)
[Change] ipset_load() and ipset_update() now log per-set "loading/updating
      set $name from $source" before processing begins, providing visibility
      into which set is being loaded during long ipset operations
      (functions.apf)
[Change] valid_ip_cidr(), valid_host(), ipt_for_host() replaced echo|grep
      subprocess calls with bash builtins ([[ =~ ]] and [[ == *pattern* ]]);
      eliminates 2-6 fork+exec calls per invocation in hot validation paths
      (functions.apf)
[Change] trust_protect_ipv6() and trust_restore_ipv6() converted from echo
      return to variable-return (_TPV6_RESULT, _TRV6_RESULT); eliminates 1
      subshell fork per advanced trust entry across 12 call sites in
      allow_hosts/deny_hosts (functions.apf)
